sensor /ˈsɛnsə/

(sensors) 

1. N-COUNT A sensor is an instrument which reacts to certain physical conditions or impressions such as heat or light, and which is used to provide information. 传感器 

例： The latest Japanese vacuum cleaners contain sensors that detect the amount of dust and type of floor. 日本最新款吸尘器装有传感器，能测出灰尘量和地板类型。

